  "body": "When a node runs the initial sync service, it first checks for stored state and if there is stored state it defaults to a regular sync. A PR would handle nodes who are only partially synced , and are not synced with the latest head of the current chain. \r\n\r\nThis would involve modifying this portion of the initial-sync service:\r\n```golang\r\n if stored {\r\n\t\tlog.Info(\"Chain state detected, exiting initial sync\")\r\n\t\treturn\r\n\t}  \r\n```",
